LATURO LANGUAGE
===============

Laturo (Lature in English) is a constructed language (conlang) using the 
Rochopelic Root System (also called The Ropelic Spelling System).

LANGUAGE STRUCTURE
------------------
- Root System: Rochopelic (independent, not derived from Latin/English/Spanish/French)
- Alphabet: 26 basic letters + 10 extended characters (á é í ó ú ñ ç ü ö ä)
- Grammar: 6 cases, 6 tenses, 4 moods, 3 genders
- Vocabulary: 10,000+ words for professional and daily conversations
- Word Order: Subject-Verb-Object (SVO)

FILE STRUCTURE
--------------
/laturo/
  - main.lang: File structure documentation
  - list.sp: Pure file list

/settings/
  - alphabits.lang: Complete alphabet and character system
  - grammar.lang: Complete grammar rules and structure
  - words.lang: 10,000+ vocabulary words
  - oldlist.lang: Archaic/obsolete words (pre-1900s-2000s)
  - banned.lang: Moderation guidelines
  - dataset.lang: AI training conversation examples

CAPITALIZATION RULES
---------------------
- First letter of sentences: ALWAYS capitalized
- Person's names / Given names: ALWAYS capitalized (NOT capitalizing is DISRESPECTFUL)
- Middle of words: NEVER capitalized
- All other words: lowercase only

EXAMPLE SENTENCE
----------------
Varminá do ela vo vim tinará?
(How do you speak this language?)

